WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:14.880 align:middle line:90%


00:00:14.880 --> 00:00:19.590 align:middle line:84%
>> I call my dog Buddhafly
because I have a fondness

00:00:19.590 --> 00:00:25.980 align:middle line:84%
for things Buddhist, and I
love butterflies very, very,

00:00:25.980 --> 00:00:26.780 align:middle line:90%
very much.

00:00:26.780 --> 00:00:29.460 align:middle line:90%


00:00:29.460 --> 00:00:37.430 align:middle line:84%
Butterflies are the
embodiment of what

00:00:37.430 --> 00:00:45.710 align:middle line:84%
happens after you go through a
great turmoil and you emerge,

00:00:45.710 --> 00:00:52.640 align:middle line:84%
you emerge stronger, more
beautiful, courageous

00:00:52.640 --> 00:00:54.690 align:middle line:84%
because of what
you've been through.

00:00:54.690 --> 00:00:58.113 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:58.113 --> 00:01:13.300 align:middle line:90%


00:01:13.300 --> 00:01:18.520 align:middle line:84%
This Halloween, I chose a
skeleton onesie with roses

00:01:18.520 --> 00:01:25.030 align:middle line:84%
on it, and I picked it because
how much more vulnerable

00:01:25.030 --> 00:01:31.390 align:middle line:84%
can one be than to say
you're seeing everything

00:01:31.390 --> 00:01:35.360 align:middle line:84%
and have it still be legal to
walk around like that in public?

00:01:35.360 --> 00:01:38.804 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:38.804 --> 00:01:45.200 align:middle line:90%


00:01:45.200 --> 00:01:53.780 align:middle line:84%
I've always wanted to be able
to unzip my proverbial chest

00:01:53.780 --> 00:01:56.840 align:middle line:90%
to show my heart.

00:01:56.840 --> 00:01:59.610 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes I used to
wear it on my sleeves,

00:01:59.610 --> 00:02:05.370 align:middle line:84%
but to actually show my
heart is to bear my soul.

00:02:05.370 --> 00:02:08.690 align:middle line:84%
And that's what I
do with my poetry.

00:02:08.690 --> 00:02:12.620 align:middle line:84%
Some may read it and think
it's egoic or narcissistic

00:02:12.620 --> 00:02:15.860 align:middle line:90%
or it's all about my story.

00:02:15.860 --> 00:02:20.270 align:middle line:90%
Well, it is my story.

00:02:20.270 --> 00:02:26.130 align:middle line:84%
But it's more about I have
an opportunity to express it,

00:02:26.130 --> 00:02:27.330 align:middle line:90%
and so do you.

00:02:27.330 --> 00:02:30.760 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:30.760 --> 00:02:43.020 align:middle line:90%


00:02:43.020 --> 00:02:45.780 align:middle line:90%
"Valid Footprint.

00:02:45.780 --> 00:02:50.850 align:middle line:84%
I had reduced and reused
and recycled so much,

00:02:50.850 --> 00:02:54.390 align:middle line:90%
I nearly made myself obsolete.

00:02:54.390 --> 00:02:57.300 align:middle line:84%
There is a need
for me to be here.

00:02:57.300 --> 00:03:00.660 align:middle line:10%
My footprint is also valid.

00:03:00.660 --> 00:03:03.344 align:middle line:90%
I won't tiptoe."

00:03:03.344 --> 00:03:06.732 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:03:06.732 --> 00:03:13.520 align:middle line:90%


00:03:13.520 --> 00:03:17.360 align:middle line:84%
If you want to hear a story,
I've got one, a huge one,

00:03:17.360 --> 00:03:20.180 align:middle line:90%
on pain.

00:03:20.180 --> 00:03:24.230 align:middle line:10%
So one Thanksgiving holiday,
I went with a group of friends

00:03:24.230 --> 00:03:30.320 align:middle line:10%
to Blackcomb, by Whistler,
in British Columbia, Canada.

00:03:30.320 --> 00:03:34.400 align:middle line:84%
I was skiing around, and
at the base of the run,

00:03:34.400 --> 00:03:39.260 align:middle line:84%
another skier came
and T-boned me.

00:03:39.260 --> 00:03:41.320 align:middle line:90%
My head hit the compacted snow.

00:03:41.320 --> 00:03:45.580 align:middle line:90%


00:03:45.580 --> 00:03:49.180 align:middle line:84%
Go forward a couple of
weeks, and one night, I

00:03:49.180 --> 00:03:51.850 align:middle line:84%
stepped in the shower,
and I popped my neck.

00:03:51.850 --> 00:03:54.730 align:middle line:90%


00:03:54.730 --> 00:03:57.010 align:middle line:84%
And immediately I had
red and blue strobing

00:03:57.010 --> 00:03:59.980 align:middle line:84%
lights in my peripheral vision,
and my left arm went numb.

00:03:59.980 --> 00:04:01.455 align:middle line:90%
And I fell to my knees.

00:04:01.455 --> 00:04:04.856 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:04:04.856 --> 00:04:10.820 align:middle line:90%


00:04:10.820 --> 00:04:14.450 align:middle line:84%
And this is where I have
to make the story short,

00:04:14.450 --> 00:04:17.600 align:middle line:90%
because it's huge.

00:04:17.600 --> 00:04:22.280 align:middle line:90%
I had a migraine for 14 years.

00:04:22.280 --> 00:04:26.040 align:middle line:84%
It's also called a new
daily persistent headache.

00:04:26.040 --> 00:04:28.760 align:middle line:90%
It's very rare.

00:04:28.760 --> 00:04:33.330 align:middle line:84%
But I was in chronic
physical pain,

00:04:33.330 --> 00:04:37.970 align:middle line:84%
and physical pain
often can be invisible.

00:04:37.970 --> 00:04:39.360 align:middle line:90%
You're not on crutches.

00:04:39.360 --> 00:04:41.120 align:middle line:90%
You're not in a wheelchair.

00:04:41.120 --> 00:04:46.050 align:middle line:84%
You don't have a shaved head
and scars, but you hurt.

00:04:46.050 --> 00:04:49.452 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:04:49.452 --> 00:05:01.130 align:middle line:90%


00:05:01.130 --> 00:05:07.070 align:middle line:84%
My life, as it had
been so broad and full,

00:05:07.070 --> 00:05:10.850 align:middle line:84%
just narrowed and narrowed
and narrowed and narrowed.

00:05:10.850 --> 00:05:18.990 align:middle line:84%
And who I was as a person who
was not who I was any longer.

00:05:18.990 --> 00:05:22.455 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:05:22.455 --> 00:05:32.370 align:middle line:90%


00:05:32.370 --> 00:05:40.100 align:middle line:84%
At the 14-year mark, when I was
at the lowest of my depression

00:05:40.100 --> 00:05:47.990 align:middle line:84%
and I had felt whittled to an
aspect of me that I didn't want

00:05:47.990 --> 00:05:53.880 align:middle line:84%
to live with any more,
I fell to my knees,

00:05:53.880 --> 00:05:58.180 align:middle line:84%
threw up by the roses
at my old house.

00:05:58.180 --> 00:06:01.631 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:06:01.631 --> 00:06:14.460 align:middle line:90%


00:06:14.460 --> 00:06:16.930 align:middle line:84%
I still have the
scars on my knees,

00:06:16.930 --> 00:06:19.500 align:middle line:90%
and those are important to me.

00:06:19.500 --> 00:06:28.720 align:middle line:84%
Because, one, when I was
willing to sacrifice myself,

00:06:28.720 --> 00:06:29.820 align:middle line:90%
the headaches stopped.

00:06:29.820 --> 00:06:33.460 align:middle line:90%


00:06:33.460 --> 00:06:35.200 align:middle line:90%
And I'm a writer.

00:06:35.200 --> 00:06:37.630 align:middle line:90%
I'm a poet.

00:06:37.630 --> 00:06:41.680 align:middle line:84%
I'm a poet whose favorite
word is "ineffable,"

00:06:41.680 --> 00:06:45.460 align:middle line:84%
and the favorite definition I've
ever heard is that which is "too

00:06:45.460 --> 00:06:47.850 align:middle line:90%
holy to be spoken."

00:06:47.850 --> 00:06:54.550 align:middle line:10%
I, who love words, have
found it quite difficult

00:06:54.550 --> 00:06:58.480 align:middle line:10%
to put into words what
happened, because I

00:06:58.480 --> 00:07:03.310 align:middle line:10%
don't think of it as an
otherworldly, Yeatsian fairies

00:07:03.310 --> 00:07:10.510 align:middle line:10%
and the little people or
capital or small G god.

00:07:10.510 --> 00:07:20.290 align:middle line:84%
I just think that somehow it
was a nondenominational miracle,

00:07:20.290 --> 00:07:28.063 align:middle line:84%
that once I was willing,
everything shifted.

00:07:28.063 --> 00:07:31.650 align:middle line:90%


00:07:31.650 --> 00:07:36.270 align:middle line:10%
And I've written a poem,
called Miracle Witness,

00:07:36.270 --> 00:07:39.176 align:middle line:10%
about this experience.

00:07:39.176 --> 00:07:42.368 align:middle line:90%


00:07:42.368 --> 00:07:45.610 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:07:45.610 --> 00:07:48.500 align:middle line:84%
"One dark night, when
the moon climbed,

00:07:48.500 --> 00:07:55.390 align:middle line:84%
I fell in a puddle by the pink
roses, a voluntary sacrifice.

00:07:55.390 --> 00:08:01.480 align:middle line:10%
After which everything,
everything, shifted,

00:08:01.480 --> 00:08:08.500 align:middle line:10%
The pain miraculously lifted
and rose to join the moon.

00:08:08.500 --> 00:08:12.130 align:middle line:84%
With new guides at my
side, I plied new skills

00:08:12.130 --> 00:08:14.740 align:middle line:84%
to become the
architect of my soul.

00:08:14.740 --> 00:08:18.970 align:middle line:84%
Finally, on the other side
of pain, with brighter days

00:08:18.970 --> 00:08:20.530 align:middle line:90%
in focus.

00:08:20.530 --> 00:08:24.310 align:middle line:84%
Rebuilding after traumas
is a solo journey

00:08:24.310 --> 00:08:27.340 align:middle line:90%
that can't be done alone.

00:08:27.340 --> 00:08:30.190 align:middle line:84%
We recount our
stories to remember

00:08:30.190 --> 00:08:36.020 align:middle line:84%
that we survived to answer
the burning question--

00:08:36.020 --> 00:08:41.316 align:middle line:90%
What miracle am I?"

00:08:41.316 --> 00:08:44.760 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:08:44.760 --> 00:08:59.530 align:middle line:90%


00:08:59.530 --> 00:09:04.180 align:middle line:84%
I don't think we can ever really
know another person's story.

00:09:04.180 --> 00:09:09.580 align:middle line:84%
If we stop at the surface,
we just get that view.

00:09:09.580 --> 00:09:13.650 align:middle line:84%
And some people don't
want to dive in,

00:09:13.650 --> 00:09:17.980 align:middle line:84%
and some people have barriers up
that they don't want to express.

00:09:17.980 --> 00:09:23.130 align:middle line:84%
But what I learned after living
14 years with chronic pain

00:09:23.130 --> 00:09:29.100 align:middle line:84%
is that I'm an extremely
much more empathetic person

00:09:29.100 --> 00:09:31.740 align:middle line:90%
to those who are struggling.

00:09:31.740 --> 00:09:41.520 align:middle line:84%
And since I rebuilt my
life, one of my deepest joys

00:09:41.520 --> 00:09:47.880 align:middle line:84%
is acknowledging the suffering
of others and bringing levity.

00:09:47.880 --> 00:09:52.740 align:middle line:84%
When I say I live here in what
I call my lighthouse, that's not

00:09:52.740 --> 00:09:54.860 align:middle line:90%
just candles, that's levity.

00:09:54.860 --> 00:10:01.180 align:middle line:90%


00:10:01.180 --> 00:10:05.910 align:middle line:84%
My purpose is to
be a lighthouse.

00:10:05.910 --> 00:10:10.220 align:middle line:84%
And a lighthouse doesn't
tell boats where to go.

00:10:10.220 --> 00:10:13.410 align:middle line:90%
It just is.

00:10:13.410 --> 00:10:20.560 align:middle line:84%
And by shining its light,
it helps provide passage

00:10:20.560 --> 00:10:22.830 align:middle line:90%
that others find their way.

00:10:22.830 --> 00:10:26.570 align:middle line:90%


00:10:26.570 --> 00:10:32.600 align:middle line:84%
And when you are who
you are and others

00:10:32.600 --> 00:10:41.660 align:middle line:84%
feel lighter from having
interacted with you, keep going.

00:10:41.660 --> 00:10:44.612 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:10:44.612 --> 00:10:59.400 align:middle line:90%


00:10:59.400 --> 00:11:06.880 align:middle line:84%
I'm more childlike now, and
that's a necessity for me.

00:11:06.880 --> 00:11:08.955 align:middle line:90%
I know it might seem strange.

00:11:08.955 --> 00:11:12.070 align:middle line:90%


00:11:12.070 --> 00:11:14.510 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't say
it's a regression,

00:11:14.510 --> 00:11:19.960 align:middle line:90%
but it's a continuation.

00:11:19.960 --> 00:11:22.100 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't that I had
an unhappy childhood.

00:11:22.100 --> 00:11:23.510 align:middle line:90%
I had a great childhood.

00:11:23.510 --> 00:11:27.410 align:middle line:84%
Lots of things happened
here that changed me,

00:11:27.410 --> 00:11:30.340 align:middle line:84%
but the big one was
the ski accident.

00:11:30.340 --> 00:11:40.060 align:middle line:84%
So on the other side of that I
just try to be a good person.

00:11:40.060 --> 00:11:43.399 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:11:43.399 --> 00:11:48.660 align:middle line:90%


00:11:48.660 --> 00:11:52.780 align:middle line:84%
I'll be driving my car,
and when I stop at a light,

00:11:52.780 --> 00:11:54.780 align:middle line:90%
I see people in traffic.

00:11:54.780 --> 00:11:58.500 align:middle line:84%
And their brows are
all furrowed like this.

00:11:58.500 --> 00:12:01.350 align:middle line:84%
And I'll roll my
window down, and I'll

00:12:01.350 --> 00:12:04.170 align:middle line:90%
take my little bubble wand.

00:12:04.170 --> 00:12:06.180 align:middle line:10%
And I'll put it out
the window, and I'll

00:12:06.180 --> 00:12:09.695 align:middle line:10%
turn it on so that when they
come around that corner--

00:12:09.695 --> 00:12:13.042 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:12:13.042 --> 00:12:16.870 align:middle line:90%


00:12:16.870 --> 00:12:22.840 align:middle line:84%
The magic is I get to
watch their faces change.

00:12:22.840 --> 00:12:27.710 align:middle line:84%
They go from hurt [GIBBERS],
worries, stress, bills,

00:12:27.710 --> 00:12:33.290 align:middle line:90%
children, war, bubbles.

00:12:33.290 --> 00:12:36.650 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:12:36.650 --> 00:12:39.540 align:middle line:90%


00:12:39.540 --> 00:12:46.530 align:middle line:84%
I love to see them taken out of
the rut and routine of things

00:12:46.530 --> 00:12:50.560 align:middle line:84%
and come alive for a moment
and then pass that on,

00:12:50.560 --> 00:12:52.210 align:middle line:90%
and then they pass that on.

00:12:52.210 --> 00:12:54.730 align:middle line:84%
And it just is the gift
that gives forward.

00:12:54.730 --> 00:12:58.216 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:12:58.216 --> 00:13:22.140 align:middle line:90%


00:13:22.140 --> 00:13:23.923 align:middle line:84%
The world is an
incredible place.

00:13:23.923 --> 00:13:26.590 align:middle line:90%


00:13:26.590 --> 00:13:34.120 align:middle line:84%
It's here for you and your
uniqueness to enjoy it.

00:13:34.120 --> 00:13:36.080 align:middle line:90%
So show up as you.

00:13:36.080 --> 00:13:39.010 align:middle line:90%
The world needs you as you are.

00:13:39.010 --> 00:13:41.800 align:middle line:90%
I'm unique, and you're unique.

00:13:41.800 --> 00:13:44.830 align:middle line:90%
And they're unique.

00:13:44.830 --> 00:13:46.390 align:middle line:90%
Be it.

00:13:46.390 --> 00:13:50.205 align:middle line:84%
Each morning I wake up and
I say, I get to be me today.

00:13:50.205 --> 00:13:53.125 align:middle line:90%


00:13:53.125 --> 00:13:56.590 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:13:56.590 --> 00:14:06.090 align:middle line:90%


00:14:06.090 --> 00:14:06.890 align:middle line:90%
"Rainbow.

00:14:06.890 --> 00:14:10.560 align:middle line:90%


00:14:10.560 --> 00:14:12.840 align:middle line:90%
I like who I'm becoming,

00:14:12.840 --> 00:14:15.870 align:middle line:84%
The growing boldness
of my voice,

00:14:15.870 --> 00:14:19.950 align:middle line:84%
That I'm not shying
away from being myself.

00:14:19.950 --> 00:14:26.700 align:middle line:84%
I like living boldly
and firmly and lovingly

00:14:26.700 --> 00:14:33.364 align:middle line:84%
And kindly and
sillily, just as I am.

00:14:33.364 --> 00:14:35.272 align:middle line:90%
[DOG WHIMPERS]

00:14:35.272 --> 00:14:36.710 align:middle line:90%


00:14:36.710 --> 00:14:40.430 align:middle line:84%
When I shift too much
to accommodate others,

00:14:40.430 --> 00:14:45.140 align:middle line:84%
to please and not
ruffle feathers,

00:14:45.140 --> 00:14:50.830 align:middle line:84%
It feels like a denial
that splinters the whole.

00:14:50.830 --> 00:14:55.330 align:middle line:10%
It's one thing to be a
chameleon, to alter one's colors

00:14:55.330 --> 00:14:59.020 align:middle line:10%
to each new environment,

00:14:59.020 --> 00:15:04.350 align:middle line:10%
It's another to live as
the rainbow one already is.

00:15:04.350 --> 00:15:08.580 align:middle line:84%
Who doesn't pause to
admire a rainbow?"

00:15:08.580 --> 00:15:11.930 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:15:11.930 --> 00:15:35.000 align:middle line:90%